author: Jacob Cheris
title: Soaking-up the excitement: DHS swimmers ready to dive into 2024 season
text:
Soaking-up the excitement: DHS swimmers ready to dive into 2024 season
New Dickinson High coach encourages positive energy, teamwork, ‘family’ vibes
DICKINSON — The excitement continues to build on the pool deck for the Dickinson Midgets’ girls swim and dive team as they have their first meet on Saturday, Sept. 7 for the Capital City Invite in Bismarck.
The Midgets will be competing against six high schools at the BSC Aquatic and Wellness Center in 12 different races: three relays, one diving event and six individual races. The top-16 swimmers will score points.
A big storyline heading into the 2024 season for DHS is the beginning of the Amy Smith era. Smith was named the new head coach of the Midgets back in July, taking over for Jenna Wolf after eight seasons at the helm.
ADVERTISEMENT
Practices at the West River Community Center have been energetic and exciting, according to Smith, and swimmers have fed off her positive energy and mindset while adjusting to the changes she has made.
“I think with change there can be some challenges, but the girls have been very positive throughout each week, and have embraced trying some new things throughout practice,” Smith said. “I see them encourage each other and cheer each other on and also push each other during practice.”
While Smith has a plethora of experience coaching at the high-school level, there will be an adjustment period for her as she has not been on the pool deck in quite some time. Throughout her career as a swimmer and coach, one value instilled in her has remained constant: Work together as one big family.
“I think that there's still a few things that I need to learn, as far as what all comes with the meets, but the swimming environment stays the same and the competition level stays the same,” Smith said. “I think some of the pieces that we've been talking about is that we're all in this together. We are one swim family. We're here to support each other and cheer each other on and be a positive light in every person on our team.”
Last season, the Midgets came in fourth in the WDA championship and seventh in the state meet. However, they made some history last season. Senior Taylor Miller broke the 100m freestyle school record with a time of 54.67 and is looking to break another record in her final season as a Midget.
She will be participating in the 100-free again but will be competing in the 200m individual-medley, the 200m free relay and the 400m free relay.
The Capital City Invite kicks off at 10 a.m. MDT at the BSC Aquatic and Wellness Center.

author: Davide Falcioni
title: Gli Stati Uniti condurranno attacchi di rappresaglia contro obiettivi iraniani in Iraq e Siria
text:
Gli Stati Uniti condurranno attacchi di rappresaglia contro obiettivi iraniani in Iraq e Siria
Gli Stati Uniti condurranno una serie di attacchi di rappresaglia contro milizie sciite sostenute dall'Iran in Siria e Iraq. A dirlo questa sera il segretario alla Difesa americano, Lloyd Austin, confermando che i raid verranno effettuati in più giorni. Il comandante del Pentagono ha spiegato che la misura costituirà una risposta agli attacchi di droni che domenica scorsa
hanno causato la morte di tre soldati USA e il ferimento di altre decine nella base militare Tower 22, in Giordania. Quei raid, ha specificato sempre Austin, sono stati condotti utilizzando droni di fabbricazione iraniana.
Parlando ad una conferenza stampa al Pentagono, Austin ha detto: "Daremo una risposta a più livelli e avremo la capacità di replicare più volte. Adotteremo tutte le azioni necessarie per difendere gli Stati Uniti, i nostri interessi e il nostro popolo. Risponderemo dove, quando e come decideremo". Il Segretario alla Difesa ha sottolineato che gli Stati Uniti non sono in guerra con l’Iran e Washington non sa se Teheran fosse a conoscenza degli specifici attacchi di droni di domenica scorsa organizzati da quella che ha descritto come l’asse della resistenza. Austin ha dichiarato comunque che "non ha importanza poiché sappiamo che l’Iran sponsorizza questi gruppi e li finanzia, e in alcuni casi li addestra".
La risposta degli Stati Uniti all'attacco a Tower 22 era attesa, tuttavia Joe Biden e altri funzionari della difesa hanno affermato che Washington non sta cercando una guerra più ampia con l’Iran o un’escalation delle tensioni nella regione. "Non è quello che cerco", ha detto il Presidente USA ai giornalisti alla Casa Bianca all'inizio di questa settimana. I piani di risposta approvati, secondo quanto riferito, dovrebbero prendere di mira obiettivi iraniani in Siria e Iraq, ma non dovrebbero interessare il territorio dell'Iran.

author: TDT
title: San Pedro sampaguita planting boosted
text:
LAGUNA — The sampaguita industry in San Pedro City here has received a huge lift from its lone representative to enrich the environment and uplift the livelihood of residents of the city.
San Pedro Lone Representative Ann Matibag disclosed that she has intensified Sampaguita planting programs all over San Pedro early this year reviving the city as the Philippines’ Sampaguita capital with the support of Senator Loren Legarda.
“We are optimistic that the Sampaguita industry will continue to bloom nationwide with our project,” said the lawmaker.
This comes as Matibag — together with volunteer residents, teachers, school personnel, barangay officials and Tulong Panghanapbuhay sa Ating Disadvantaged/Displaced Workers personnel — planted sampaguita on vacant lots, schools and other venues in the 27 barangays to sustain one of the city’s main livelihood programs throughout the years.
Matibag also disclosed that they had partnered with the School District Office that already started last year to plant sampaguita in school gardens as she encouraged her fellow lawmakers to support the local sampaguita industry.

title: 推进人工智能安全治理 构建安全可信发展生态--"有益 安全 公平"人工智能向善论坛举行-新华网
text:
新华网上海7月30日电（记者李峰洲）在刚刚落下帷幕的2025世界人工智能大会上，一场以“有益 安全 公平”为主题的人工智能向善分论坛备受关注，其讨论度和热度一直从会场内延展到了会场外。尤其是本次论坛呼应《全球人工智能治理倡议》提出的“智能向善”核心理念，通过汇聚各方智慧，分享实践经验，共同探索人工智能健康有序发展之路。
　　论坛由中国网络空间安全协会主办，人工智能行业领域相关政府部门、研究机构、企业管理及技术人员约150余人参会。国家互联网应急中心负责人受邀参加论坛，并以“人工智能安全治理技术探索与实践”为题做了主旨发言。
　　相关负责人介绍，国家互联网应急中心落实国家关于加强人工智能安全治理的最新要求，开展了全方位的人工智能安全治理技术探索和实践。在支撑人工智能安全监管方面，着力构建事前事中事后全生命周期的技术支撑体系；在促进人工智能发展方面，构建了以AI治理AI的安全测评体系与平台，持续面向社会发布中文互联网基础语料库；在保障人工智能安全方面，建设了CNVD人工智能漏洞子库，开展大模型产品漏洞众测活动，构建了人工智能服务安全测试基准数据集；在推动人工智能应用方面，持续组织AI赋能网络安全应用测试活动，研制了基于大模型的语料清洗过滤模型；在国际交流合作方面，针对国际网络安全应急响应普遍需求研制了基于AI的网页仿冒监测发现系统，在2024年互联网大会乌镇峰会上发布《人工智能赋能网络安全应急响应合作倡议》，提出了自主可控、公平合法、安全可靠、数据隐私的可信人工智能准则，并组织来自16个国家的专家开展国际交流研讨。
　　国家互联网应急中心将持续研究人工智能治理新技术，探索行业共治共享新模式，携手共创人工智能可信安全发展生态，促进人工智能行业高质量发展。
